##I'm worried about the baby. I don't know if I'M GONNA learn

Micro Signal Xiezuozheyunshegong

FUNCTION INTRODUCTION: Volunteer Information Management, social worker information management, public welfare information release, social work professional exchange

This article is one of the case interviews conducted by the collaborators in the "Peasant Workers' anti-epidemic Rescue Action" , aiming at quickly identifying the vulnerable groups and their needs in the epidemic situation, and providing reference for the epidemic prevention, control and rescue work, we put it together and share it with you.

Deep breathing in case of an outbreak
A case study on the plight of migrant workers in Foshan (III)

I'm worried about the kids. I don't know if they're still in school
DICTATION: Dazhen (not his real name) / Anhui nationality
Place of employment: Nanjing
Editor's Note: Dazhen, Male, 57, suffered from cerebral infarction and high blood pressure. He and his wife worked together in Nanjing to look after his granddaughter Xin Xin (not his real name) . Xin Xin's father passed away and her mother remarried. My wife works as a janitor. The two old men persisted day after day so that their granddaughter could study in Nanjing.
Before, Xinxin's parents all worked in Nanjing. Xinxin's father committed suicide because he couldn't repay the loan due to loan sharks. Xinxin's mother left when Xinxin was eight months old. Since then, Xinxin has been raised by me and her grandmother to support her to go to school, she is also our two old people's life hope and depend on.

I usually collect some waste products nearby, collect other people's unwanted clothes, household appliances and so on to sell. First Xinxin grandma is also to help me collect waste, later around the neighbors all know, by others introduced, Xinxin grandma just had the job of cleaning. Grandma Xin and I don't have social security... When we get old, I think it doesn't matter where we are, we don't know what to do when we go back home, we can't farm when we're old, and farming in the countryside is now all mechanized, take it and put it on the ground. And now farming investment is quite big, 1,000 yuan per mu of land harvest, input 500-600 yuan of cost, plus labor costs, hard quarter to earn money, also grow what outlet. I said to her grandmother, you find a job, rent enough, to live, a little bitter is nothing. Since the Spring Festival, grandma has no holiday, need to clean up the health, also do not know how the Spring Festival wages, recently has not been paid.

Co-author social worker visits big Caesar's home (Autumn 2018)

Spring Festival generally we do not go home, such as children will soon be on holiday when the ticket is very difficult to buy, will not choose to go back during the Spring Festival. I'm old, I have cerebral infarction and high blood pressure, and my body often hurts. In February 2018 had a disease, can only return home hospital treatment, Nanjing Medicine Expensive, also reluctant to buy. Now sometimes dizzy, usually to eat blood pressure medicine, a box to get dozens of dollars, every time back home is also to buy medicine, will save money, reluctant to eat, can resist a little bit is a little bit. If you buy medicine in Nanjing, the monthly expenditure is about 500 yuan, in our family is not afford to spend. Xin Xin grandma work more tired, often back pain, also can not walk for a long time. I thought I'd buy her a used tricycle so she wouldn't be so tired.

I was in Nanjing in 2003 during SARS. This outbreak is almost the same as SARS. At that time, no measures, just say SARS, what exactly is not clear; now advanced technology, through watching television, how many people died are very clear. But this disease I feel is equivalent to the plague, found after the report to the National Health Commission, it seems to be transferred to the experts to study. I felt there was no need to panic, as long as I could figure out what was wrong, there must be a way; something like the simplest toothache had to be done. But I've been watching the news, and I haven't figured it out yet. As for the kit, I know whether it's a negative or a positive test. It should be positive. It's COVID-19. Now which supermarket mask can not buy, near the supermarket all write out of stock, fortunately grandma work there property has hair, home before there is a little spare.

Co-author social worker visits big Caesar's house (spring 2019)

The main effect on us at the moment is that we can't go out. My job is to pick up waste, take to the recycling station to sell, the Spring Festival waste recycling station was not open, estimated the tenth day is not open, I do not know when to open. Now there is no one out, also can not pick up waste, today someone called me to collect waste, I do not know where to put. I don't know what I would have done if the outbreak had lasted any longer, and now I'm stuck at home, but I'm more worried about my kids'education. Now Leave School for some days, you look at her, she will go to study; Not Adult Care Her, learn for a while not to learn. This period of time off, the mood of the child is lazy, do not get up in the morning, habit formation is a big problem.

A handwritten curriculum for children in distress (Autumn 2019)

Xin Xin doesn't pay attention to her study and looks pitiful. The last final examination language test can, math and English is not good, no one tutorship, take the children we old people also have no way.

The child will soon be promoted to junior high school, do not know there is no school can go up, if there is school, I and grandma so old age in Nanjing to work hard are worth!

Social Worker's notes

After talking with GRANDPA on the phone, I can feel his helplessness and hope. He was worried about his grandmother's health and about his granddaughter's studies. The sudden outbreak of the epidemic, the children delayed the start of school, school work without guidance, habit formation... are the most concerned about GRANDPA. In the face of their own cultural level by the limitations of knowledge and culture, there are practical problems, GRANDPA had to bow his head. But he is still optimistic about the epidemic, as long as the children have school, the future can still look forward to!

Service Recommendations:
Now:

1. COVID-19;
2. Regular follow-up on the living conditions of families, the health of the elderly, and the next step of life planning;
3. To provide on-line homework assistance to co-workers, to meet the learning needs of the elderly and to help them develop good sleeping habits during childhood outbreaks;
4. Follow up grandma's salary issue, provide employment information support and legal support;
5. Link resources to provide microfinancing.

LONG-TERM:

In conjunction with the collaborator's struggling children's self-help library project, the Companion Angel Project:
1. Continue to provide financial aid to students
2. Invite Xinxin to participate in self-service library's weekend visit every weekend, provide her with homework guidance, interest classes, answer questions, and enhance her interest in learning;
3. Connect one-on-one with the angels to respond to the individualized needs of Xinxin's growth
Link Health Care Volunteers to provide health and medical support, medical services, and medical assistance.
